<template>
   <hero :title="title" :viewName="viewName" :links="links" :tagline="tagline"/>
</template>
<script>
import hero from '@/components/hero.vue'

export default {
  name: 'dasha',
  components: {
    hero
  },
  data () {
    return {
      title: 'Dasha Utyuzh',
      tagline: 'Web Developer',
      viewName: 'home',
      links: ['About', 'Resume', 'Portfolio', 'Contact']
    }
  },
  metaInfo: {
    title: 'Dasha Utyuzh', // set a title
    titleTemplate: '%s  ← Front End Developer', // title is now "My Example App  ← My Site!"
    htmlAttrs: {
      lang: 'en',
      amp: undefined // "amp" has no value
    },
    meta: [
      {name: 'description', content: 'Front End Web Developer based out of Cleveland, Ohio.'}
    ]
  }
}
</script>
<style lang="scss">
  #app {
    padding: 0;
  }
</style>
